#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:3
msgid "Copy Scale Constraint"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:6
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:8
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Copy Scale` constraint forces its owner to have the same "
"scale as its target."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:13
msgid ""
"Here we talk of **scale**, not of **size**! Indeed, you can have two "
"objects, one much bigger than the other, and yet both of them have the same "
"scale. This is also true with bones: in :guilabel:`Pose` mode, they all have"
" a unitary scale when they are in rest position, represented by their "
"visible length."
msgstr ""

