msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:27
msgid "Copy Scale panel"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:39
msgid "Target"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:31
msgid ""
"This constraint uses one target, and is not functional (red state) when it "
"has none."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:36
msgid "Bone"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:34
msgid ""
"If :guilabel:`Target` is an :guilabel:`Armature`, a new field is displayed "
"offering the optional choice to set an individual bone as "
":guilabel:`Target`."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:36
msgid "Head/Tail"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:37
msgid ""
"If a :guilabel:`Bone` is set as :guilabel:`Target`, a new field is displayed"
" offering the optional choice of where along this bone the target point "
"lies."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:39
msgid "Vertex Group"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:39
msgid ""
"If :guilabel:`Target` is a :guilabel:`Mesh`, a new field is displayed "
"offering the optional choice to set a :guilabel:`Vertex Group` as target."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:42
msgid "X, Y, Z"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:42
msgid ""
"These buttons control along which axes the scale is constrained - by "
"default, it is enabled along all three."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:45
msgid "Offset"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:45
msgid ""
"When enabled, this control allows the owner to be scaled (using its current "
"transform properties), relatively to its target's scale."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:51
msgid "Space"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/constraints/transform/copy_scale.rst:48
msgid ""
"This constraint allows you to choose in which space to evaluate its owner's "
"and target's transform properties."
msgstr ""
